---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout page="about">
  <!-- ================= ABOUT SECTION ================= -->
  <section id="about" class="w-full bg-section-bg">
    <div
      class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20 text-center"
    >
      <div class="flex justify-center mb-4 sm:mb-6">
        <span class="w-16 sm:w-20 lg:w-24 h-[2px] bg-primary rounded"></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-primary mb-6 sm:mb-8">
        About Srila Prabhupada
      </h2>

      <p
        class="text-text-body text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-4xl mx-auto"
      >
        ISKCON is a non-profit organization that works for social welfare. He
        was a genuine holy person with enormous integrity and compassion, and he
        had a powerful impact on those who met him.
      </p>

      <p
        class="text-text-body text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed mt-4 sm:mt-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto"
      >
        He never claimed authority and respect for himself; what he said and did
        was always in the name of Krishna.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-6 sm:mt-8 text-text-body text-sm sm:text-base font-medium">
        â€” Dr Thomas J. Hopkins.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= EARLY LIFE ================= -->
  <section id="early-life" class="w-full bg-primary text-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-center mb-8 sm:mb-10 lg:mb-14"
      >
        Early Life
      </h2>

      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 sm:gap-10 lg:gap-12 items-center"
      >
        <div class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed order-2 lg:order-1">
          <p>
            On 1st September 1896, Abhay Charan Bhaktivedanta Swami Srila
            Prabhupada was born in a Hindu family. After a few decades, he met
            the well-known religious leader and scholar Shri Srila
            Bhaktisiddhanta Saraswati Thakur in 1922, who educated Abhay Charan
            to introduce the philosophies of Lord Krishna to the West. The
            influence of Srila Bhaktisiddhanta Saraswati's philosophy became a
            turning point in his life. In 1933, Srila Prabhupada became a
            follower of Srila Bhaktisiddhanta and spent the next 32 years making
            his journey toward the western countries to fulfill his mentor's
            command.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end order-1 lg:order-2">
          <img
            src="../assets/images/early-life.png"
            alt="Early Life"
            class="max-w-full h-auto object-contain"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= EXPANDING BOUNDARIES ================= -->
  <section class="relative bg-white py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-primary-hover"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-primary-hover"></div>

    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h2
        class="text-center text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-primary-hover mb-8 sm:mb-10 lg:mb-12 font-bold"
      >
        Expanding Boundaries
      </h2>

      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 sm:gap-10 lg:gap-12 items-center"
      >
        <div class="flex justify-center order-1 md:order-1">
          <img
            src="../assets/images/expanding.png"
            alt="Expanding Boundaries"
            class="max-w-full h-auto object-contain"
          />
        </div>

        <div
          class="text-primary-hover text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium order-2 md:order-2"
        >
          <p>
            At 69, Srila Prabhupada put his footsteps in New York City with only
            Rs40 in his pocket, a trunk full of books, and some personal
            belongings. He faced great hardships, and the journey was
            treacherous without any money to survive and a steady place to live.
            But Srila Prabhupada remained determined and didn't give up. Thus,
            he began his mission humbly by giving classes on the Bhagavad-gita
            in lofts in the Bowery (New York's infamous skid row) and leading
            kirtan (traditional devotional chants) in Tompkins Square Park.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div
      class="hidden md:block absolute right-0 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 opacity-20 overflow-hidden"
    >
      <img
        src="../assets/images/decorative-pattern.png"
        alt=""
        class="w-48 lg:w-64 object-contain"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= MESSAGE TO SOCIETY ================= -->
  <section id="message-to-society" class="w-full bg-primary text-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
      <h2
        class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-center mb-8 sm:mb-10 lg:mb-14 font-semibold"
      >
        His Message to Society
      </h2>

      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 sm:gap-10 lg:gap-12 items-center"
      >
        <div class="text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed order-2 lg:order-1">
          <p>
            Srila Prabhupada's message of peace and goodwill resonated strongly
            with the hippie community and younger generation; some even came
            forward to become serious students of the Bhakti-yoga (loving
            devotion to God) tradition. With the help of his students and
            followers, he rented a small piece of land and registered his
            organization officially. On 11th July 1966, he formally established
            the ISKCON or International Society for Krishna Consciousness. In
            the next 11 years, he circled the entire world around 14 times and
            conveyed the teachings of Lord Krishna to countless people on six
            different continents.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end order-1 lg:order-2">
          <img
            src="../assets/images/hismessage.png"
            alt="Srila Prabhupada Message to Society"
            class="max-w-full h-auto object-contain"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= ACHIEVEMENTS ================= -->
  <section class="bg-white py-12 sm:py-14 lg:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <!-- Heading at Top -->
      <h2
        class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-primary mb-6 sm:mb-8 text-center"
      >
        His Achievements
      </h2>

      <!-- Image Section -->
      <div class="mb-8 sm:mb-10 lg:mb-12 flex justify-center">
        <img
          src="../assets/images/hisachivements.png"
          alt="Temple"
          class="w-full max-w-4xl rounded-lg sm:rounded-xl lg:rounded-2xl shadow-lg object-cover"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Text Content AFTER Image -->
      <p
        class="text-base sm:text-lg lg:text-xl text-red-700 mb-4 sm:mb-6 leading-relaxed text-justify"
      >
        Srila Prabhupada came back to India with a wish to cultivate the better
        roots of Lord Krishna. He opened numerous temples and one of the largest
        centers of ISKCON in the holy towns of Mayapur and Vrindavana. The most
        imperative contribution of Srila Prabhupada is conceivably his books. He
        wrote more than 70 volumes on the tradition of Krishna, which scholars
        highly appreciate because of its depth, clarity, and faithfulness toward
        the tradition. Several colleges have used his work in textbooks, and all
        his books have been already translated into 76 different languages.
      </p>

      <p
        class="text-base sm:text-lg lg:text-xl text-red-700 mb-4 sm:mb-6 leading-relaxed text-justify"
      >
        His lifetime achievements are innumerable, magnificent, and
        extraordinary. Some of his achievements are listed below:
      </p>

      <ul
        class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 sm:space-y-3 mb-6 ml-4 sm:ml-6 text-red-700 text-base sm:text-lg lg:text-xl leading-relaxed"
      >
        <li>He dictated a total of 22,000 pages of text.</li>
        <li>
          He translated and wrote purports to 18,000 verses of Srimad Bhagwatam
          and 700 verses of Srimad Bhagwat Gita.
        </li>
        <li>
          He translated and wrote purports to 700 verses of the Srimad Bhagwat
          Gita and 12,555 verses of Chaitanya Charitamrit.
        </li>
        <li>
          He published 147 books, wrote 7,000 letters to his disciples, and
          brought his magazine <em>Back to Godhead</em> into the mainstream with 1
          million copies distributed.
        </li>
        <li>
          His Bhagavad Gita lectures are compiled in 7 volumes, and Srimad
          Bhagwatam in about 12 book volumes.
        </li>
        <li>
          His conversations with scientists, professors, and editors were
          compiled in 42 volumes, along with innumerable recordings.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div
        class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-primary p-4 sm:p-6 mt-8 sm:mt-10"
      >
        <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-text-body font-semibold">
          At the age of 70, he began the mission to bring Lord Krishna's name to
          every household. In the short span of 9 years, he inspired 5,000
          devotees and established 108 ISKCON temples worldwide.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
